MasterControl: Manufacturing Solutions (Mx) Conversion Rate 
Increase
Business Problem
MasterControl provides quality and manufacturing management software to life sciences 
organizations, including pharmaceutical, biotechnology, and medical device 
manufacturers. While the company’s Quality Solutions (Qx) product line has achieved a 
strong conversion rate of 19.7%, the newer Manufacturing Solutions (Mx) product line has 
realized a significantly lower conversion rate of 12.7%. This gap indicates that Mx is 
underperforming relative to both internal benchmarks and business expectations.
As MasterControl seeks to expand into new markets with Mx, the company faces a critical 
challenge: it lacks a clear understanding of which customer segments are most likely to 
convert for this newer solution. Without precise insight into high-potential customer profiles, 
sales and marketing resources may be misallocated toward prospects with a low likelihood 
of conversion, limiting revenue growth and slowing market adoption.
Business Objectives
The primary objective is to increase the Mx conversion rate by identifying, prioritizing, and 
targeting customer profiles that are most likely to progress through the sales funnel. 
Specifically, MasterControl aims to understand:
• Which industries, manufacturing models, site functions, and company sizes are 
best suited for Mx
• Which job titles, seniority levels, and functional roles are most influential in driving 
sales progression
• Which existing Qx customers are most likely to adopt Mx as an additional solution
Benefit of a Solution
A data-driven approach to identifying high-potential Mx customers will enable 
MasterControl to:
1. Increase Mx conversion rates and sales efficiency
2. Expand and better monetize its existing customer base
3. Optimize sales and marketing resource allocation by prioritizing high-probability 
leads
4. Refine and formalize ideal customer profiles for both new and cross-sell 
opportunities
