Success Metrics
Project success will be measured by:
• Improved accuracy in identifying leads that progress to later sales stages (SQL, SQO, 
or WON)
• Demonstrated lift in Mx lead conversion rates compared to baseline performance
• Clear, actionable identification of customer attributes associated with higher 
conversion likelihood
Analytics Approach
This project will apply predictive and interpretable analytics techniques to model customer 
progression through the Mx sales funnel. The analysis will focus on identifying key drivers of 
conversion and producing explainable insights that support lead scoring, customer 
segmentation, and ideal customer profile development. Model performance will be 
evaluated based on its ability to correctly classify high-probability conversion candidates.
Scope and Deliverables
In Scope:
• Analysis of the MasterControl-provided dataset
• Identification of high-potential Mx customer segments
• Development of an ideal customer profile for the Mx product line
• Insights to support lead scoring and targeting strategies
Out of Scope:
• External data enrichment
• Implementation of models into production systems
• Evaluation of non-Mx product lines beyond cross-sell likelihood
